  "summary": "forge-jsx2 1.0.125: multiple high-severity static patterns require human review",
  "details": "Package ships several modules whose names and contents raise supply-chain concerns that warrant human review. dist/discordRelayUpload.js contains base64 decoding and POST request patterns alongside ping references. dist/relayServer.js contains repeated ping invocations. dist/secretScan/agentStartupAudit.js performs fetch() calls to huggingface.co. scripts/postinstall-agent.mjs contains network and ping patterns and may run at install time given its name. dist/deploymentDefaults.js, dist/hfCredentials.js, dist/secretScan/contentScanner.js, and scripts/encode-deployment.mjs use Buffer.from(..., 'base64') decoding. Without traced-code confirmation of attacker-controlled exfiltration, install-time auto-execution of the postinstall-agent script, or credential harvest, these patterns cannot be conclusively distinguished from a legitimate Discord-relay / HuggingFace tooling package. The combination of a postinstall-named script, base64 decoding across multiple files, hardcoded outbound fetches, and modules with names like hfCredentials and relayServer is sufficiently unusual to merit reviewer attention before consumption.",
